anime.my_comments:
Generic, bland and dull Isekai. It may look different than the run-of-the-mill isekai through its designs and the fact the main cast are the villains of the story, nevertheless all this is trivial at best. Momonga may look as a skeleton but you can change the body of the character with a kid and it wouldn't change nothing, he acts just like the generic nice guy harem protagonist. Also, the anime reminds us constantly he isn't bad through his softie inner voice in his head whenever he talks or says something "evil". Saying all this, I must say Overlord is another run-of-the-mill isekai which contributes absolute nothing to the genre.
First Season: Momonga is an incredibly boring character, aside of describing what's happening on the screen he really does not have much personality. He is so OP that no conflict is ever relevant- Momonga's powerful enough to just solve it easily without any effort. The MMO backdrop is unnecessary tho, it could been just him trapped in a fantasy world and would've worked perfectly. About the side cast, their personalities are about as interesting as a rock.; You just need to know they absolutely adore Momonga. About the pacing- see, I love slow paced shows because they have time to develop his characters without rush and gives the show the posibility of being dialogued-based instead of action-based. Here, the pace is very slow and they don't develop a shit, if it does, its on an irrelevant character, dialogues aren't interesting and there is really no quality content on the entire show because also the fights are bad lol. To kinda summarize the show, first quarter spends on the introduction of characters that have no personality outside of sucking up momonga's tinkywinky. Second quarter is spent on Momonga defeating an army of literally nobodies that wont matter nor affect the rest of the story in any way. The third quarter much of the same and the last one is Momonga vs one of his minions.
Second Season: The first season was boring but kinda watchable, however the second one... the show tries to develop characters no one cares about that first appeared on the previous episode and the show/episode/arc becomes insufferably dull. First season had a slow pace which wasn't that bad, this one is ten times slower and worse. Entire episodes are dedicated to characters we don't have a reason to care about. The first three episodes (the lizard-focused ones) are unwatchable and a waste of time. Action scenes were meh, Madhouse isn't what it was before, his action scenes now rely on zoom shots, motion tweens and jarring CGI. Art is ugly, the soundtrack si mediocre and the I really dislike the opening.
